						<summary>

						<p>This is much worn out. It records some provision (gift of sheep) for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple by one <hi rend="bold">Pālai Ēṟkuṭṭi</hi> a merchant of Tāmaraippūṇḍi a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Umbaḷa-nāḍu. Tirumaṛaikkāḍu was also in the same <hi rend="italic">nāḍu.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
